### Grant EnvironmentAdmin role to a Service Principal on a non-DV environment
###
### For non-Dataverse (sandbox-SKU) Power Platform environments where the SPN
### can't be added via PPAC's "Application Users" UI (no Dataverse to host
### them). This file works with the VS Code REST Client extension:
###   https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=humao.rest-client
###
### Steps:
###   1. Fill in the @-variables below (one per line; whitespace matters)
###   2. Run "Step A" first to capture the current baseline
###   3. Run "Step B" to add the EnvironmentAdmin role
###   4. Re-run "Step A" to verify the SPN now appears
###
### CRITICAL: spnObjectId must be the Service Principal's Object ID from
### Azure portal → Enterprise applications, NOT the App Registration's
### Object ID. They are different GUIDs even though they refer to the
### "same" SPN. Using the wrong one produces a 400 "Principal not found".

# --- BAP base URL per ring (uncomment exactly one) ---------------
# Prod:    @baseUrl = https://api.bap.microsoft.com
# Preprod: @baseUrl = https://tip1.api.bap.microsoft.com
# Test:    @baseUrl = https://tip2.api.bap.microsoft.com
@baseUrl       = https://tip1.api.bap.microsoft.com

@apiVersion    = 2021-04-01
@tenantId      = <YOUR TENANT GUID>
@envId         = <TARGET ENVIRONMENT GUID>
@spnObjectId   = <SERVICE PRINCIPAL Object ID — from Enterprise Applications>

# Get the userToken by signing in as a user with EnvironmentAdmin on this env:
#   az login --tenant <tenantId>
#   az account get-access-token --resource https://service.powerapps.com/ --query accessToken -o tsv
# Token lifetime is ~1 hour; refresh as needed.
@userToken     = <BEARER TOKEN>


### =================================================================
### Step A — list current role assignments (baseline check)
### =================================================================
GET {{baseUrl}}/providers/Microsoft.BusinessAppPlatform/scopes/admin/environments/{{envId}}/roleAssignments?api-version={{apiVersion}}
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
Accept: application/json


### =================================================================
### Step B — assign EnvironmentAdmin to the SPN
### =================================================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/providers/Microsoft.BusinessAppPlatform/scopes/admin/environments/{{envId}}/modifyRoleAssignments?api-version={{apiVersion}}
Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "add": [
    {
      "properties": {
        "roleDefinition": {
          "id": "/providers/Microsoft.BusinessAppPlatform/scopes/admin/environments/{{envId}}/roleDefinitions/EnvironmentAdmin"
        },
        "principal": {
          "id": "{{spnObjectId}}",
          "type": "ServicePrincipal",
          "tenantId": "{{tenantId}}"
        }
      }
    }
  ],
  "remove": []
}


### =================================================================
### Step C — (optional) remove the role if you need to clean up
### =================================================================
# POST {{baseUrl}}/providers/Microsoft.BusinessAppPlatform/scopes/admin/environments/{{envId}}/modifyRoleAssignments?api-version={{apiVersion}}
# Authorization: Bearer {{userToken}}
# Content-Type: application/json
#
# {
#   "add": [],
#   "remove": [
#     {
#       "properties": {
#         "roleDefinition": {
#           "id": "/providers/Microsoft.BusinessAppPlatform/scopes/admin/environments/{{envId}}/roleDefinitions/EnvironmentAdmin"
#         },
#         "principal": {
#           "id": "{{spnObjectId}}",
#           "type": "ServicePrincipal",
#           "tenantId": "{{tenantId}}"
#         }
#       }
#     }
#   ]
# }
